A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Sickle Cell Disease – Specialized Clinics and Scholarship
3 Program for Medical Residents
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Maryland Department of Health to establish certain
5 specialized clinics for the management and treatment of sickle cell disease and
6 establish a scholarship program for medical residents with a certain specialization
7 and focus on sickle cell disease; and generally relating to sickle cell disease.
8 BY adding to
9 Article – Health – General
10 Section 18–510 and 18–511
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – Health – General
16 18–510.
17 (A) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH THREE SPECIALIZED
18 CLINICS DEDICATED TO THE MANAGEMENT AND TREATMENT OF SICKLE CELL
19 DISEASE.
20 (2) THE CLINICS ESTABLISHED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
21 SUBSECTION SHALL BE LOCATED IN:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
